Arctic pine logs are cut from arctic pines, found on the island of Neitiznot. A Woodcutting level of 54 is required to cut them, giving 40 experience per log; 42 Firemaking is needed to make a fire using these type of logs, granting 125 experience per log. A Woodcutting level of 56 is required to split these logs.

They are also used to make Fremennik round shields, requiring a level of 56 in Woodcutting. Two of these logs, a bronze nail, and a rope are required to make one, granting 34 Crafting experience.

Players can also use the logs on a woodcutting stump to make split logs for the quest The Fremennik Isles.

'''Arctic pine logs''' are cut from [[arctic pine]]s, found on the island of [[Neitiznot]]. A [[Woodcutting]] level of 54 is required to cut them, giving 40 experience per log; 42 [[Firemaking]] is needed to make a fire using these type of logs, granting 125 experience per log. A Woodcutting level of 56 is required to split these logs.

They are also used to make [[Fremennik round shield]]s, requiring a level of 56 in Woodcutting. Two of these logs, a [[bronze nail]], and a [[rope]] are required to make one, granting 34 [[Crafting]] experience.

Players can also use the logs on a [[woodcutting stump]] to make [[split log]]s for the quest [[The Fremennik Isles]].
